1. Wire the digit commons (cathodes)

Connect each digit pin directly to an Arduino digital pin (we’ll “enable” a digit by driving it LOW because CC sinks current through the digit pin):

Display pin 12 (D1) → Arduino D10

Display pin 9 (D2) → Arduino D11

Display pin 8 (D3) → Arduino D12

Display pin 6 (D4) → Arduino D13

2. Wire the segments (via resistors)

Each segment pin goes through a 220–330 Ω resistor to an Arduino pin. (SevSeg will drive segments HIGH to light them on CC.)

a : Display pin 11 → resistor → Arduino D2

b : Display pin 7 → resistor → Arduino D3

c : Display pin 4 → resistor → Arduino D4

d : Display pin 2 → resistor → Arduino D5

e : Display pin 1 → resistor → Arduino D6

f : Display pin 10 → resistor → Arduino D7

g : Display pin 5 → resistor → Arduino D8

dp: Display pin 3 → resistor → Arduino D9 (optional; skip if you don’t need decimal points)